1. A universal document converter
  http://pandoc.org/index.html
  
2. Bibtex4Word is an add-in for Microsoft Word that allows the citation of references and the insertion of a bibliography into your document using your choice of formatting style.
  http://www.ee.ic.ac.uk/hp/staff/dmb/perl/index.html
  
3. Export your Excel table as latex markup which can be pasted into an existing tex document
  http://www.ctan.org/tex-archive/support/excel2latex/
  
4. Export your word document into tex file
  http://www.wordtolatex.com/
  http://www.word2tex.com/
  
5. Help you understand the meaning of commands.
  http://www.emerson.emory.edu/services/latex/latex_toc.html
  
6. Just draw the symbol you are looking for into the square area above and look what happens!
  http://detexify.kirelabs.org/classify.html
  
7. LaTeX命令速查手册（包括手册1-6）
